----------------------------------------------------------------------
README
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Gmsh example for an acoustic model with (quadratic) hex-27 elements.

requires:
 * Gmsh       - for downloading, see http://gmsh.info
 * pygmsh     - python wrapper, see https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pygmsh
 * numpy      - scientific computing with python, see http://www.numpy.org


tested for:
- python 3.7: Gmsh version 4.0, pygmsh version 6.0.2, numpy version 1.18.1

0. installation:
  
   - Gmsh:
       download Gmsh and install package (make sure that command gmsh is in your PATH)
       http://gmsh.info

   - pygmsh:
       for installation using pip, type:
       > pip install -U pygmsh
   
   (finally check your installation, see if you can run a simple pygmsh example: https://github.com/nschloe/pygmsh)

1. to generate mesh, type:

    > ./mesh_example_with_Gmsh.py


2. run simulation:
    
   - run script:
     > ./run_this_example.sh


Compare your seismograms in OUTPUT_FILES/ with the reference ones in directory REF_SEIS/

